Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @carrot{1} and grate on the coarse side
of your #grater{}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Zest,
then halve the @lime{1/2}. Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, remove the
seeds then finely chop. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium heat. Once
hot, add the pepper and cook until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and
cook for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}. Add the
@water{300%ml}(for the rice) and @chicken stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil,
lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for
~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to
the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a #medium frying pan{} over medium heat (no oil!) Once hot, add
the @desiccated coconut{25%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly
toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Watch it like a hawk as it can burn easily.

When golden, transfer to a #bowl{}. We will add it to the rice later. Wipe out
the pan and return it to a medium-high heat - it's time to cook the duck!

Pat the @duck breasts{2} dry with #kitchen paper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands
after handling raw duck and its packaging. Season the duck on both sides with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. When the #frying pan{} is hot, lay the
duck in the pan (no oil), skin-side down, fry until the skin is golden,
~{5%minutes}. Turn, cook for ~{1%minute} on the flesh side to seal the meat.
Remove to a #baking tray{}, skin-side up, and roast on the top shelf of your
oven until cooked, ~{15%minutes}.

> The duck is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from your oven and rest in a warm place, (covered loosely
in #tin foil{} if you have some) for ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, give the frying pan a quick wash and then pop back on a low heat.
Add the @mango chutney{80%g} along with the @water{2%tbsp}(for the glaze). Heat,
stirring, until the mixture bubbles then cook for ~{2%minutes} until shiny and
sticky. Remove from the heat and stir in a pinch of @?chilli{pinch} and a squeeze
of @lime juice{from the remaining lime}.

When the duck is ready, remove from the oven and transfer to the pan with the
glaze. Roll the duck in the glaze and leave to rest while you plate up. Fluff
up the rice with a #fork{} and stir in the carrot, lime zest, half the
coriander, the remaining lime juice and coconut. Season to taste with salt and
pepper if needed, then share between your plates. Thinly slice the duck breasts
and lay alongside. Spoon the remaining glaze over the duck. Finish by
sprinkling over the remaining coriander and a little more chilli. Enjoy!